  "body": "/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nCurrent context was set to cluster1.\r\nRan `kubectl config view --minify --context=cluster2` and got back information about cluster1 instead.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nI expected the output to be the cluster2 information\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nHave two contexts in your kube config, A and B\r\nRun `kubectl config use-context A` to set A as current context\r\nRun `kubectl config view --minify --context=B`\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\nI'd like to help contribute, so if this is an easy fix, someone point me in the right direction and I'll try to get it done.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.10.2\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release): MacOS 10.11.6\r\n- Install tools: kubectl was installed via brew\r\n",
